<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-29T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-29T15:00:00-05:00" n="945" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d945">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72115/2701a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-29T15:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1916, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3722. General interest in the United States in matter of Belgian
                            deportation continues to increase, and it is important that Department
                            be advised what action, if any, the German Government has taken in
                            response to the appeals and protest of this Government in addition to
                            the action reported in your 4756 of December 20.<note n="2" xml:id="d945fn2">
                                <ref target="frus1916Supp#pg_870">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 870</ref>.</note> Take matter
                            up immediately with <persName corresp="#p_ZDA1">Zimmermann</persName>
                            and report by cable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>